subSubSection.paragraph:
Description. (based primarily on the 
holotype
) Body elongate, compressed; depth at dorsal origin about 4 1/2 in SL and slightly larger than HL. Dorsal profile of body nearly horizontal past dorsal fin, straight between dorsal-fin origin and snout; abdomen rounded anteriorly, indistinct midventral keel extends from level of pelvic-fin origin to vent; vent located at anal-fin origin. Lateral line complete, with short branches extending obliquely above and below for entire length. Vertebral column with 45 to 47 vertebrae and 11 or 12 ribs.
